Several alcohol traders are working with strippers to boost their business profits. SOWETO - Sowetans no longer have to travel to that spot near the Noord taxi rank to see exotic dancers; it is secretly being provided at a number of venues in the township. During the day all seems above board at these businesses, but wait until darkness settles in. Young people in flashy vehicles wearing expensive international clothing brands pack these drinking spots on "show days", mostly Thursdays, a day referred to as "Ladies Night" or "PhuzaThursday". There is no entrance charge at most of these places, but you have to dig deep into your pocket to buy beverages. A 330ml bottle of beer ranges between R20 and R25 but those willing to spend more go for vodka or cider. But patrons are not really bothered by the prices, they come for the "entertainment".